<plot>Griffin, a brilliant biomechanical engineer, revolutionized the world of medicine by creating a new lifesaving heart valve. But when he discovered a manufacturing flaw, the corporation convinced him to stay quiet as hundreds of hearts stopped beating. After realizing no punishment provided by our courts could ever give him what he deserves, Griffin descends into a world of overwhelming guilt and anguish. When he meets Kate, a woman suffering from his mistake, he realizes there is a chance for salvation. Can Griffin save himself by saving her?</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?019779</url></doc>
